other_tests.findings: Endometrium 8.8 mm thick and homogeneously echogenic; fluid and echogenic material thought to be blood present in the cavity; 5 to 10 simple cysts present in the right ovary.
Lesion 2.8 cm by 2.4 cm by 2.4 cm, isointense to gray matter, extending into the suprasellar region, mild compression and possible invasion of the right cavernous sinus, mild patchy enhancement.

other_tests.changes_over_time: Normal results of visual-field tests. Rapid diminishing or resolution of signs and symptoms of acromegaly.
